-- Monte Paschi rights suspended limit-down on 1st day of share sale
-- 
-- Mon Jun 09, 2014 03:18AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, June 9 (Reuters) - Rights in Italian lender Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena <BMPS.MI> fell as much as 10 percent and were suspended in early trade on Monday as a 5-billion euro ($6.8 billion) share sale started.

The rights were last indicated at 20.7 euros against a closing level of 23.1 euros adjusted for the share sale on Friday.